SIMPLE: miscarry
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Miscarry
<hw>Mis*car"ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Miscarried</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Miscarrying</conjf>.]</vmorph>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To carry, or go, wrong; to fail of reaching a
destination, or fail of the intended effect; to be unsuccessful; to
suffer defeat.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>My ships have all <qex>miscarried</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The cardinal's letters to the pope <qex>miscarried</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To bring forth young before the time they are
viable; to have a spontaneous abortion.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Miscast</ent>⟦br⟧
